---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Double & Triple Word Score Combos — Multi-Premium Strategies" description="Master double-double and triple-triple word score combinations in Scrabble. Learn how to hit multiple premium squares for 4x and 9x word multipliers." keywords="double word score scrabble, triple word score, double double scrabble, triple triple scrabble, premium square strategy, multi premium combos">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Double & Triple Word Score Combos in Scrabble","description":"Master multi-premium square strategies for massive scoring in Scrabble.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-double-triple-word-combos"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you hit two premium squares with one word in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes — if a word spans multiple premium squares, all bonuses apply. A word covering two DWS squares gets 4x total (doubled twice). A word covering two TWS squares theoretically gets 9x, though this is extremely rare due to board geometry."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does a double-double work in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A double-double occurs when your word covers two Double Word Score squares simultaneously. The word's total is doubled once for the first DWS, then doubled again for the second — giving 4x the base score. A 20-point word becomes 80 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the maximum score from premium squares?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The theoretical maximum from premium squares alone is a triple-triple (9x multiplier) combined with DLS tiles. A high-value word on a triple-triple with Z on a DLS could score 200+ points in a single turn. Tournament records confirm 300+ point single turns."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Double & Triple Word Score Combos — Multi-Premium Mastery</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Landing on one premium square is good. Landing on two is game-changing. When a single word spans multiple word-multiplier squares, the bonuses stack multiplicatively — a double-double gives 4x, and the legendary triple-triple gives 9x. Understanding these combos separates recreational players from competitive scorers.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4×</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Double-Double</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6×</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Double-Triple</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9×</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Triple-Triple</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">300+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Record pts/turn</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How Multi-Premium Scoring Works</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Rule</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Word multipliers stack <span class="text-white font-medium">multiplicatively</span>, not additively. DWS + DWS = 2×2 = 4× (not 2+2=4). TWS + TWS = 3×3 = 9× (not 3+3=6). This is why multi-premium plays produce astronomical scores.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 Double-Double (4×)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Word covers 2 DWS squares. A 15pt word becomes 60pts. Most achievable multi-premium combo.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 Triple-Triple (9×)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Word covers 2 TWS squares. A 15pt word becomes 135pts. Extremely rare but game-ending.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ Double-Triple (6×)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Word covers 1 DWS + 1 TWS. A 15pt word becomes 90pts. Uncommon but realistic.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ DLS + Word Multi</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">High-value tile on DLS + word on DWS/TWS. The DLS applies first, then the word multiplier amplifies it.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Board Geometry for Multi-Premiums</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Double-Double paths:</span> DWS squares are spaced so a 5-7 letter word can span two of them. Look at the diagonal corners of the inner board square — words running through these hit two DWS naturally.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Triple-Triple theory:</span> TWS squares sit in the corners and mid-edges. A word connecting two corner TWS squares needs to be 15 letters (the full board width) — only possible through multiple plays. But edge TWS-to-TWS gaps are 7 squares — achievable with a bingo.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Setup is key:</span> Multi-premium plays rarely happen by accident. You need to plan 1-2 turns ahead — place a word that opens a path to two premiums, then strike with a long word on the next turn.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Maximising Premium Square Value</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Scoring Order</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-cyan-900/50 border border-cyan-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-cyan-300 font-bold">1</span><p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Apply DLS/TLS to individual tile values first</p></div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-cyan-900/50 border border-cyan-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-cyan-300 font-bold">2</span><p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Sum all tile values (with letter bonuses applied)</p></div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-cyan-900/50 border border-cyan-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-cyan-300 font-bold">3</span><p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Apply first word multiplier (DWS or TWS)</p></div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-cyan-900/50 border border-cyan-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-cyan-300 font-bold">4</span><p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Apply second word multiplier (stacked multiplicatively)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/understanding-premium-squares/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Understanding Premium Squares</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-triple-word-score-strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Triple Word Score Strategy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scoring-100-points-single-turn/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scoring 100+ Points in a Single Turn</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find high-scoring words for premium squares — free solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
